        <h1>EVALZZ</h1>
        <h3>Unified AI Profiles for Smarter Tech Hiring</h3>
        <p>Investor Presentation</p>
        <p>Hammad Ali | July 2025</p>
      </section>

      <!-- Slide 2: Problem Statement -->
      <section>
        <h2>Problem</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Fragmented candidate data across LinkedIn, GitHub, Twitter, Medium, YouTube</li>
          <li>Recruiters lack deep technical insights; relying on resumes alone</li>
          <li>Cumbersome multi-tool workflows for sourcing, assessing, and scheduling</li>
          <li>Low transparency and trust in candidate authenticity</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Slide 3: Market Opportunity -->
      <section>
        <h2>Market Opportunity</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Indian tech hiring market: ~$2B SaaS spend (est.)</li>
          <li>Rapid growth in AI-driven HR tools</li>
          <li>High demand for quality tech talent—enterprises & startups</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Slide 4: Solution Overview -->
      <section>
        <h2>Solution: EVALZZ</h2>
        <p>An end-to-end SaaS platform that:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Aggregates data from multiple sources into one unified profile</li>
          <li>Uses AI to assess and rate candidates on technical dimensions</li>
          <li>Verifies projects via live coding and peer reviews</li>
          <li>Matches candidates to roles with intelligent filtering and scoring</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Slide 5: Core Features -->
      <section>
        <h2>Core Features</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Unified Candidate Profiles (LinkedIn, GitHub, Twitter, Medium, YouTube)</li>
          <li>AI-Based Multi-Dimensional Ratings (Code Quality, Writing, System Design)</li>
          <li>Verified Projects & Peer Reviews with Authenticity Badges</li>
          <li>Intelligent Profile Matching & Filtered Search</li>
          <li>Built-In Collaboration & Scheduling Tools</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Slide 6: Competitive Differentiators -->
      <section>
        <h2>Competitive Differentiators</h2>
        <ol>
          <li>Deep technical analysis: code pattern & static review</li>
          <li>Visual scoring: radar charts & skill badges</li>
          <li>Full workflow: sourcing → assessment → collaboration</li>
          <li>Profile portability & trust via verified badges</li>
          <li>Regional language support & learning recommendations</li>
        </ol>
      </section>

      <!-- Slide 7: Technology Stack -->
      <section>
        <h2>Technology Stack</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Frontend: React + Tailwind CSS</li>
          <li>Backend: Node.js/Express + Flask APIs</li>
          <li>Database: MongoDB (JSON profiles)</li>
          <li>AI/ML: Transformers (BERT, T5), Code analysis libs (ESLint, static analyzers)</li>
          <li>Cloud: AWS (EC2, S3), Docker, Kubernetes</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Slide 8: Business Model -->
      <section>
        <h2>Business Model</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>SaaS Subscription: tiered by active roles & features</li>
          <li>Per-assessment fees for coding tests & peer reviews</li>
          <li>Enterprise plans with custom integrations & SLAs</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Slide 9: Go-to-Market Strategy -->
      <section>
        <h2>Go-to-Market Strategy</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Partnerships with recruitment agencies & HR consultancies</li>
          <li>Digital marketing & thought leadership on LinkedIn</li>
          <li>Free trial & pilot programs with mid-sized enterprises</li>
          <li>Presence at HR tech events & webinars</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

